# Git workflow — branch, PR, review

## When to branch (before any code changes)

Create a new branch when the task adds or changes **behavior** — features, fixes, refactors, infra/CI.

Skip branching for: questions, read-only exploration, trivial doc typos (unless user asks to PR it).

## Naming

`feat/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `chore/`, `ci/` + short kebab-case description.

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git checkout -b feat/short-description
```

## Before marking done

1. `make lint && make test`
2. Commit + `git push -u origin HEAD`
3. `gh pr create` → `main` (PR template auto-fills)
4. Return PR URL; **do not merge** without user approval

## Hard rules

- Never push to `main`
- Never merge without green CI (`python`, `frontend`) + human review
- Keep PRs ~200 LOC; split large work

Details: `CLAUDE.md` §5, branch protection: `docs/branch-protection.md`
